# Cupcake Cloudflare Tunnel Configuration
#
# RPi : copy as  /boot/firmware/cupcake-cloudflared.txt  before first boot
# VM  : copy as  /opt/cupcake/cloudflared-token.txt       before first boot
#
# The file is read on every boot but only acted on when present.
# It is deleted after the tunnel is installed.
# To re-configure a running appliance use:
#   sudo /opt/cupcake/configure-cloudflared.sh <token>
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# How to obtain a tunnel token:
#   1. Go to https://one.dash.cloudflare.com
#   2. Networks → Tunnels → Create a tunnel → Cloudflared
#   3. Name the tunnel (e.g. "cupcake-lab")
#   4. In the install step, copy the token from the --token flag shown
#      in the connector command. It starts with  eyJ...
#   5. Configure the tunnel Public Hostname in the Cloudflare dashboard:
#        Subdomain : <your choice>
#        Domain    : <your domain>
#        Service   : HTTP  http://localhost
#
# The appliance serves the cupcake webgui by default for all tunnel traffic.
# Cloudflare handles TLS — no certificate changes are needed on the appliance.
#
TUNNEL_TOKEN=eyJhIjoixxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
